SPICULES. Megascleres: Tylostyles slightly curved (
Fig. 6A
), 1300–(1962)–2200 μm long and 10– (17.42)–25 μm thick. Long, smooth and thin styles, with shaft slightly thickened in distal third (
Fig. 6B
), 1200–(1500)–1800 μm long and 2.5–(3.3)–5 μm thick. Styles to tylostyles or subtylostyles more or less bent near head as true rhabdostyles (
Fig. 6C
), 460–(505)–590 μm long and 10–(15.62)–20 μm thick. Thin and sinuous styles, with round heads and slightly rounded points (
Fig. 6D
), 460–(556.5)–600 μm long and 2.5–(3.5)–5 μm thick.
